1. Login to your instance

2. sudo apt-get update

3. sudo apt-get install -y git python-pip vim

4. sudo pip install --upgrade git-review

5. git-review --version   (should be 1.25 or greater)

6. git config --global user.name "Firstname Lastname"

7. git config --global user.email youremail@example.com

8. git config --global gitreview.username yourgerritusername

9. git config --global core.editor yourfavoriteeditor


Steps while submitting a patch:

1. Create branch from the master, make changes to the required files
    git checkout -b bug/bug_number

2. Once all the changes are done:
    a. git add .
    b. git commit (if commiting for the first time) else "git commit --amend" (if commiting again to the same review)
    c. git review
    
    
